== INSTALL ==

1) Clone the repo into your computer.
2) Copy the source where you want (most of cases you'll need  more copy of the code).
3) Open the downloaded "exporter" file in your favorite text editor.
4) Add "user", "pass", "db" and "host" variables' values.

== USAGE ==
$ ./dbexporter
If it's a Drupal site, the script will check Drush, and if it's exist clear the cache tables with it.
The exported file will compress with gzip.
The exported file name will ymd_H:M_dbname.sql.gz.

== WARNING ==
Maybe you have to add execute permission to the downloaded shell script (chmod ug+x dbexporter).
